Argentina Rejects $700 Million Offer for 26% Siderar Stake, Clarin Reports

-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 
2011-04-22T11:48:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/argentina-rejects-700-million-offer-for-26-siderar-stake-clarin-reports.html
Argentina ’s President  Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner  rejected a 2.9 billion-peso ($700 million)
offer for the government’s 26 percent stake in steelmaker
 Siderar SAIC (ERAR) , Clarin reported, without saying how it obtained
the information.  Techint Group, Siderar’s controlling stakeholder, has made
several acquisition offers over the past two years, the Buenos
Aires-based newspaper said. The latest proposal was made in the
past few days as the government and the company discuss naming
state representatives to Siderar’s board, Clarin said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in Buenos Aires at 
 rorihuela@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Laura Price at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net  